{"type":"message","id":"e4e353dc","parentId":"72bda8c2","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:15:26.023Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3d9eaw5415tm_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5323\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 011439 - The TIC experiment requires implementing a classifier that identifies invariant (causal/structural) vs variant (ephemeral/contextual) content across pulse logs, then uses invariants to predict next pulse content.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"nova-shell","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5323\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 011439 - The TIC experiment requires implementing a classifier that identifies invariant (causal/structural) vs variant (ephemeral/contextual) content across pulse logs, then uses invariants to predict next pulse content.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774329326012}}
{"type":"message","id":"16bc1c6d","parentId":"e4e353dc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:15:26.029Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3d9eaw5415tm_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 011015\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: temporal_invariance_classifier.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and decide on the ONE concrete action that advances the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent state:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- A major insight: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\r\n- Next action: TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n- Need to implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action is to implement the TIC classifier. Let me look at what exists and what needs to be created.\r\n\r\nI need to:\r\n1. Check what pulse logs exist\r\n2. Implement a TIC classifier that can:\r\n   - Identify invariants vs variants in pulse content\r\n   - Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n   - Measure classification accuracy and prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nLet me create a TIC implementation. I'll need to create a new file for this - likely something like `src/tic_classifier.py` or `research/tic_experiment.py`.\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action: Create the TIC classifier implementation that can analyze pulse logs.\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script that implements the Temporal Invariance Compression classifier.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that can identify invariants vs variants across pulse logs and predict subsequent pulse content.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier implementation that analyzes pulse logs to identify temporal invariants and validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis against success criteria (>70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n- Identifies invariants vs variants across pulse sequences\r\n- Predicts next pulse content from invariant patterns\r\n- Validates COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple, Set\r\n\r\nclass TICIClassifier:\r\n    def __init__(self, logs_dir: str = \"logs\"):\r\n        self.logs_dir = Path(logs_dir)\r\n        self.pulses = []\r\n        self.invariants = {}  # token -> frequency across pulses\r\n        self.variants = {}    # token -> temporal entropy\r\n        \r\n    def load_pulses(self) -> List[Dict]:\r\n        \"\"\"Load all pulse logs sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n        pulse_files = sorted(self.logs_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n        for f in pulse_files:\r\n            content = f.read_text()\r\n            # Extract metadata and content\r\n            self.pulses.append({\r\n                \"file\": f.name,\r\n                \"content\": content,\r\n                \"tokens\": self._tokenize(content)\r\n            })\r\n        return self.pulses\r\n    \r\n    def _tokenize(self, text: str) -> List[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Simple whitespace tokenization.\"\"\"\r\n        return re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', text.lower())\r\n    \r\n    def compute_invariant_scores(self) -> Dict[str, float]:\r\n        \"\"\"Compute invariance score for each token (0=variant, 1=invariant).\"\"\"\r\n        if not self.pulses:\r\n            return {}\r\n        \r\n        n = len(self.pulses)\r\n        token_presence = Counter()\r\n        token_total = Counter()\r\n        \r\n        for pulse in self.pulses:\r\n            seen = set()\r\n            for token in pulse[\"tokens\"]:\r\n                token_total[token] += 1\r\n                if token not in seen:\r\n                    token_presence[token] += 1\r\n                seen.add(token)\r\n        \r\n        # Invariance = how many pulses contain this token\r\n        scores = {}\r\n        for token, count in token_total.items():\r\n            presence = token_presence[token]\r\n            # Score: fraction of pulses containing this token\r\n            scores[token] = presence / n\r\n        \r\n        return scores\r\n    \r\n    def classify_content(self, text: str, threshold: float = 0.7) -> Tuple[Set, Set]:\r\n        \"\"\"Classify content into invariants (high temporal persistence) and variants.\"\"\"\r\n        tokens = self._tokenize(text)\r\n        scores = self.compute_invariant_scores()\r\n        \r\n        invariants = set()\r\n        variants = set()\r\n        \r\n        seen = set()\r\n        for token in tokens:\r\n            if token in seen:\r\n                continue\r\n            score = scores.get(token, 0)\r\n            if score >= threshold:\r\n                invariants.add(token)\r\n            else:\r\n                variants.add(token)\r\n            seen.add(token)\r\n        \r\n        return invariants, variants\r\n    \r\n    def predict_next_pulse(self, prior_pulses: List[Dict]) -> Set[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Predict tokens likely in next pulse based on invariant structure.\"\"\"\r\n        if len(prior_pulses) < 2:\r\n            return set()\r\n        \r\n        # Use invariants from all prior pulses\r\n        scores = self.compute_invariant_scores()\r\n        invariants = {t for t, s in scores.items() if s >= 0.7}\r\n        \r\n        # Filter to significant tokens (appear at least twice in recent pulses)\r\n        recent_tokens = Counter()\r\n        for p in prior_pulses[-3:]:\r\n            recent_tokens.update(set(p[\"tokens\"]))\r\n        \r\n        predicted = {t for t in invariants if recent_tokens.get(t, 0) >= 2}\r\n        return predicted\r\n    \r\n    def evaluate(self) -> Dict:\r\n        \"\"\"Run TIC experiment and return metrics.\"\"\"\r\n        if len(self.pulses) < 5:\r\n            return {\"error\": \"Need at least 5 pulses for evaluation\"}\r\n        \r\n        results = {\r\n            \"total_pulses\": len(self\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 01:10:43\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774329326022}}
